hopobject.body: I'm sorry, he's amanamedicalcenter.com On December 31, 2014, the last American combat troops will rotate out of Afghanistan and the responsibility for security will be passed to the Afghan people after thirteen years of war. New Year's Day 2015 should not only bring a new relationship between the United States and Afghanistan, but it should also mark the end of the conflict that was begun in our skies on September 11, which was formalized days later when Congress passed the Authorization for Use of Military Force.
